<body>
  <h1>5S for a Safer, More Efficient Chemical Facility</h1>
  <p>The 5S methodology is a workplace organization system that can significantly improve safety, efficiency, and organization in your chemical manufacturing facility.</p>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="box">
      <h2>Sort (Seiri)</h2>
      <p>Distinguish between necessary and unnecessary items. Discard, relocate, or sell anything not essential.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
      <h2>Set in Order (Seiton)</h2>
      <p>Arrange remaining items in designated and clearly labeled locations for easy access and identification.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
      <h2>Shine (Seiso)</h2>
      <p>Maintain a clean and organized workspace. Regular cleaning prevents spills, contamination, and accidents.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
      <h2>Standardize (Seiketsu)</h2>
      <p>Establish consistent practices for the first three S's. Ensure everyone understands and follows the organization system.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="box">
      <h2>Sustain (Shitsuke)</h2>
      <p>Continuously improve and maintain good habits formed through the 5S process.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>**Benefits of 5S in Chemical Manufacturing:**</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Improved Safety</li>
    <li>Enhanced Efficiency</li>
    <li>Reduced Costs</li>
    <li>Boosted Morale</li>
    <li>Improved Quality Control</li>
  </ul>

